  <h2>This site sets zero cookies.</h2>
  <p>
    No session cookies. No persistent cookies. No first-party analytics cookies. No third-party
    cookies because there are no third-party scripts. If you open your browser's cookie inspector on
    code-rescue.com, you will see an empty list.
  </p>

  <p>
    This is deliberate. A marketing page explaining an engineering-rigor engagement does not need to
    track its readers. Everything interactive on the page — the sticky topnav, the live footer
    clock, the scroll-anchor links — runs entirely in your browser and persists nothing.
  </p>

  <h2>If you'd like to verify</h2>
  <p>
    Open devtools → Application → Cookies → <code>https://code-rescue.com</code>. The entry is
    empty.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions: <a href="mailto:max@code-rescue.com">max@code-rescue.com</a>.
  </p>
